mail-notification
------------------------------------------
Mail Notification is a status icon (aka tray icon) that
informs you if you have new mail.

It works with system trays implementing the freedesktop.org
System Tray Specification, such as the GNOME Panel
Notification Area, the Xfce Notification Area and the KDE
System Tray.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.5-1
  fetchyahoo
  getlive
  gstreamer0.10
  gstreamer0.10-plugins-base
  gstreamer0.10-plugins-gconf
  gstreamer0.10-plugins-good
  gstreamer0.10-plugins-oss
  libcamel1.2_14-2.30.1-1
  libdbus1_3-1.2.24-1
  libdbus-glib_1_2-0.86-1
  libgcc1-4.3.4-3
  libgconf2_4-2.28.1-1
  libgdk_pixbuf2.0_0-2.20.1-1
  libglade2.0_0-2.6.4-1
  libglib2.0_0-2.24.1-1
  libgmime2.4_2-2.4.17-1
  libgnome2_0-2.30.0-1
  libgnome-keyring0-2.30.1-1
  libgnomeui2_0-2.24.3-1
  libgnomevfs2_0-2.24.3-1
  libgtk2.0_0-2.20.1-1
  libintl8-0.17-11
  libnotify1-0.4.5-10
  libpango1.0_0-1.28.0-1
  libsasl2-2.1.19-3
  libX11_6-1.3.3-1
  libxml2-2.7.7-1
  openssl-0.9.8n-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.20.51-2
  cygport-0.9.84-1
  gawk-3.1.7-1
  gcc4-core-4.3.4-3
  gettext-devel-0.17-11
